Filipino cuisine.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li>Pechay can be grown from low to mid elevations throughout the year. However, production is best during the dry season.</li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b>: </p><ul><li>6-10 tons per hectares.</li></ul>','<div><br></div><ul><li>Sandy to clay loam soils.</li><li>Soil with a pH ranging from 5.5 to 6.5.</li></ul>','&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Filler
Crops&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Carrots
(Karot):&lt;/b&gt; The tall leaves of the pechay can provide some shade for the carrots,
helping to keep the soil moist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Radishes
(Labanos):&lt;/b&gt; They grow quickly and can be harvested before they start competing
heavily with the pechay for space and nutrients.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tomatoes:&lt;/b&gt;
Planting them together could lead to competition for resources and potentially
hinder the growth of both crops.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Broccoli,
Cabbage, and Cauliflower are all susceptible to the same harmful insects.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

