&lt;/b&gt;Planting them too closely together may lead to competition for resources.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Onions and
garlic&lt;/b&gt;- Some gardeners prefer to keep them separate to avoid potential flavor
interference.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common Insect Pest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Stick Bug&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Whiteflies&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Aphids&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Thrips&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt; &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;',1,'2023-10-24 02:57:38');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (15,29,9,'Chili','<p>Chili also known as \"sili\" is a type of plant with spicy fruits. It is a common plant found in the Philippines and can grow anywhere. It has a woody body and branches, and its leaves are only small and rounded at the bottom sharp at the tip. The fruit is oblong with a pointed tip, green when raw, and red when ripe.</p>','<p><b>Time of planting</b></p><ul><li><p class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"></p><p class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">May to September during the wet season and October to February during the dry season.</p></li></ul><p class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li>6-11 tons per hectares.</li></ul>','<ul><li><p class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"></p><p class=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\">Pepper grows in any type of soil.</p></li><li>It performs best in sandy loam to clay loam soils.<br></li></ul>','&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;companion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Onions and Garlic &lt;/b&gt;can deter aphids and ants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Spinach &lt;/b&gt;provides shade to the roots of your chilies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Worst companion&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cabbage and Mustard greens&lt;/b&gt; takes&amp;nbsp;away nutrients from your chili plants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Common insect pest&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ants&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Aphids&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;References:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;https://www.pinoyfoodsecurity.com/agriculture/chili-pepper-farming-in-the-philippines/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',1,'2023-10-24 02:57:40');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (19,29,1,'String Beans','<span style=\\\"text-align: justify; text-indent: 24px;\\\">    In the Philippines, string beans are locally known as \\\"sitaw.\\\" This term is widely used in markets, kitchens, and daily conversations across the country when referring to this long, slender green vegetable.</span>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li> It can be grown throughout the year.</li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li> 9-11 tons per hectares.</li></ul>','<ul><li>They can thrive in various types of soil.</li><li>Soil pH value between 5.5 to 6.8.</li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Filler Crops&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cucumber, eggplant, and radish&lt;/b&gt; These plants encourage strong bean growth, and the beans boost the nitrogen in the soil that they need to grow.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Potato &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;plants help to repel Mexican bean beetles from bean plants. In return, bean plants can repel the Colorado potato beetle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Garlic,
Onions, and chives it will stunt the growth of the beans.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common insect
pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Aphids&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Whiteflies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Pod Borers&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-06 03:36:45');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (20,27,9,'Bottle Gourd','<p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;text-indent:.25in\\&quot;\"><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\">Upo, also known as bottle gourd or calabash, is a popular vegetable in many parts of the world. It is a long, cylindrical-shaped vegetable that can grow up to 60 cm in length and has a pale green color. Upo is a warm season crop that can be grown in most tropical and subtropical regions. It is rich in vitamins, minerals, and fiber, making it a healthy addition to any diet.<o:p></o:p></span></p><div><br></div>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li> Upo can be planted throughout the year, the optimal planting periods for maximum yield and profitability are between October to December and May to July.</li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li>&nbsp;8-15 tons per hectares.</li></ul><p><br></p><div><br></div>','<ul><li>Sandy loamy soils.</li><li>Soil pH between 6.5 and 7.5.</li></ul><div><br></div>','&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler Crops&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tomatoes
(Kamatis):&lt;/b&gt; The tall growth of the tomato plants can provide some shade for the
bottle gourd.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cucumbers
(Pipino):&lt;/b&gt; They have similar water and sunlight requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Season&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cabbage,
Broccoli, Cauliflower:&lt;/b&gt; They have different nutrient requirements and can
potentially compete for resources in the soil.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Potatoes:&lt;/b&gt;
Potatoes and bitter gourds have different nutrient requirements and planting
them together may lead to competition for resources in the soil.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;





&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sweet
Potatoes: &lt;/b&gt;Sweet potatoes can be aggressive growers and may overtake bitter
gourds if planted in proximity.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Common Insect Pest&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Leaf-footed
plant bug&lt;b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Fruit rot&lt;b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Yellow
beetle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;References:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;https://www.juanmagsasaka.com/2020/12/upo-bottle-gourd-production-guide.html&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-06 04:39:36');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (21,29,1,'Tomato','<div><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"text-align: justify; \\\"><span lang=\\\"EN-US\\\">      In the Philippines, tomatoes are commonly known as \\\"kamatis.\\\"
The term \\\"kamatis\\\" is widely used to refer to tomatoes in various
contexts, whether in everyday conversation, markets, or in the context of
Filipino recipes. This word is used to describe both the fruit itself and
dishes that include tomatoes as an ingredient. The use of kamatis is prevalent
in Filipino cuisine, adding a tangy and vibrant flavor to many local dishes.<o:p></o:p></span></p></div>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li>Usually planted from September to January in hilly areas and from November to February in lowland areas.</li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li>20-30 tons per hectares.</li></ul>','<ul><li>Sandy loam and clay loam soils</li><li>Soil pH value of 5.5 to 8.0.</li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Fillers
Crops&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Carrots:&lt;/b&gt;
Carrots and peppers have different root depths, so they dont compete for
nutrients. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Corn:&lt;/b&gt; Can
provide natural support for the vining growth of patola and offer some shade to
the patola plants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Cabbage&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;



&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Potatoes:&lt;/b&gt; Recommended to avoid planting them too closely together to reduce the risk of
spreading diseases.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Common Insect Pest&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fruit worm&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Whiteflies&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thrips&lt;b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-06 04:42:22');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (23,28,1,'Broccoli','<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"text-align:justify;text-indent:.25in\\\"><span lang=\\\"EN-US\\\">In the
Philippines, broccoli is commonly known as \\\"brokoli.\\\" The term
\\\"broccoli\\\" is widely recognized and used in markets, kitchens, and
everyday conversations across the country. Broccoli is a green vegetable that
belongs to the cabbage family and is known for its dense, flowering head.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li>Month of October to December Broccoli requires soils that can provide continuous water throughout the season.<span style=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"> </span></li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li> 4 to 10 tons per hectares.</li></ul><div><br></div>','<ul><li>Well drained loamy soil.</li><li>A pH range of 6.0 to 6.5is recommended to ensure a good yield.</li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Fillers
Crops&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Onions
(Sibuyas) and Garlic (Bawang):&lt;/b&gt; Can help deter pests that might otherwise bother
broccoli. They do not compete heavily with broccoli for nutrients as they have
different nutrient requirements.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Avoid
planting corn, tomatoes, and peppers alongside broccoli, because these plants
are heavy feeders. They compete with broccoli for the same nutrients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Common insect pest&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Aphids&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Flea Beetles&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cutworms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Loopers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Caterpillars&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leaf miners&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wireworms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Moths&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Maggots&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-06 05:07:20');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (24,28,1,'Cabbage','<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"text-align: justify; \\\"><span lang=\\\"EN-US\\\">      In the Philippines,
cabbage is commonly known as \\\"repolyo.\\\" This term is used to refer to
the round-headed or cone-shaped vegetable that belongs to the Brassica family.
Repolyo is a versatile vegetable and is used in various Filipino dishes. It can
be eaten raw in salads, pickled, or cooked in stir-fries, soups, and stews.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li> (Oct-Dec) Cabbage has a high-water requirement.<span style=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"> </span></li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li> 20 to 25 tons per hectares.</li></ul>','<ul><li>Well-drained loamy soil.</li><li>A pH range of 5.6 to 7.3 is recommended to ensure a good yield.</li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Fillers
Crops&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify; &quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Onions
(Sibuyas) and Garlic (Bawang): &lt;/b&gt;Can help deter pests that might otherwise bother
broccoli. They do not compete heavily with broccoli for nutrients as they have
different nutrient requirements.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tomatoes:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;
Planting them together could lead to competition for resources and potentially
hinder the growth of both crops.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Broccoli,
Cabbage, and Cauliflower are all susceptible to the same harmful insects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Common Insect Pest&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Cutworms&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Cabbage Root Fly&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Cabbage
Looper&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-06 05:11:54');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (25,28,1,'Cauliflower','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:.25in\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">In the
Philippines, cauliflower is commonly known as \"kawolepule.\" The term
\"cauliflower\" is also widely recognized, especially in urban areas
and among English speakers.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting:</b> </p><ul><li>September to January Cauliflower is a cool weather vegetable and more sensitive to heat than other Cole crops.<span style=\\\\\\\"white-space:pre\\\\\\\">		</span> </li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li>20,000 heads.</li></ul>','<ul><li>Prefers heavy loamy soils.</li><li>Soil pH 5.5 to 7.0.</li></ul>','&lt;div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Fillers
Crops&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Onions
(Sibuyas) and Garlic (Bawang):&lt;/b&gt; Can help deter pests that might otherwise bother
broccoli. They do not compete heavily with broccoli for nutrients as they have different
nutrient requirements.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tomatoes:
