year. September to January.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\">Volume of Productivity<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p>





</p><ul style=\\\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 2rem; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\\\"><li>0.697 kt.</li></ul>','<ul><li><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\\\" 11.0pt;line-height:106%;mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\">The best soil for growing spinach is a nutrient-rich, well-drained soil mix that contains a high amount of organic matter, such as compost. To get the best soil, mix in some sand to improve the drainage and try to keep the soil slightly acidic with a pH value between 6.5-6.8.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>','&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Fillers&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Beans &lt;/b&gt;it provides shade and fix nitrogen in the soil.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Radish &lt;/b&gt;loosens the soil and deter pests.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Peas&lt;/b&gt; it gives more efficient space.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;(Cabbage,
Broccoli, Cauliflower):&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;They have different nutrient requirements and can
potentially compete for resources in the soil.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sweet
Potatoes:&lt;/b&gt; Aggressive growers and may overtake Spinach if planted in close
proximity.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common Insect Pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;color:#040C28&quot;&gt;Stink
bugs&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;color:#040C28&quot;&gt;Locusts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Arial&amp;quot;,sans-serif;color:#040C28&quot;&gt;Spider
mites&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reference:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gardeningbreak.com/best-growing-conditions-for-spinach-easy-overview/&quot;&gt;Spinach Growing Conditions: Soil, Water, Spacing, and More &ndash; Gardening Break&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://growers-planet.com/spinach-companion-plants/&quot;&gt;24 Best Spinach Companion Plants (&amp;amp; The Worst) - GP (growers-planet.com)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 04:43:53');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (42,29,9,'Water Spinach','<p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\"text-align:justify;text-indent:.25in\\\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: Tahoma, serif; font-size: 18px;\\\">Kangkong, also known as water spinach, is a leafy vegetable that grows in watery environments such as swamps and marshes. It belongs to the family of morning glory plants and is scientifically called Ipomoea aquatica.</span><br></p>','<p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\">Time of Planting</span></b></p><ul><li><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\">Kangkong can be grown all year round if the water supply is sufficient. However, it is best to plant it during the rainy season, which is from June to November.</span></li></ul><p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p>

</p><p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\">Volume of Productivity<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>','<ul><li><span style=\\\"font-family: Tahoma, serif; font-size: 18px;\\\">Kangkong thrives in moist environments with a pH level between 6-7 so adding lime can also help adjust the acidity level of the soil.</span><br></li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Filler Crops&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li data-priority=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; list-style: disc; margin: 0px 0px 0px 20px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 6px !important; padding-left: 0px;&quot;&gt;Radishes, onions, and carrots. These plants help repel pests and insects that can damage water spinach, such as aphids and flea beetles.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li data-priority=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; list-style: disc; margin: 0px 0px 0px 20px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 6px !important; padding-left: 0px;&quot;&gt;Strawberries, peas, and beans. These plants help improve the soil quality for water spinach by fixing nitrogen.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li data-priority=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 0px; list-style: disc; margin: 0px 0px 0px 20px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 6px !important; padding-left: 0px;&quot;&gt;Lettuce, kale, cauliflower, broccoli, cabbage, and eggplant. These plants have similar growing requirements and can share space with water spinach.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;(Onions,
Garlic): &lt;/b&gt;Different growth patterns and may not be compatible when planted in
close proximity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Potatoes:&lt;/b&gt;
Have different water and nutrient needs, and they may not thrive when planted
together.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common Insect Pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Aphids&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Leaf miners&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Cutworms&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Caterpillars&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Whiteflies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Thrips&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;References:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.homesandgardens.com/gardens/spinach-companion-plants&quot;&gt;Spinach companion plants: what to grow alongside spinach | (homesandgardens.com)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 04:46:24');
