pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Caterpillars&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leaf miner&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Grasshopper&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spider mites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Nematodes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 05:38:36');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (45,29,1,'Peanut','<ul><li><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\">In the
Philippines, peanuts are commonly known as \\\"mani.\\\" This term is
widely used in markets, kitchens, and daily conversations across the country
when referring to these legumes.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>','<p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\"><b><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\">Time of Planting</span></b></p><ul><li><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\" style=\"\"><li style=\"\">Peanuts can be grown throughout the year in the Philippines, as long as production inputs such as water are adequate.</li><li style=\"\">The dry-season crop (October to early November) generally gives higher yields and beans of better quality than the rainy-season crop.</li><li style=\"\">Peanuts should be planted in May and June if the season is rainy.</li></span></li></ul><p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\"><b><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p>

</p><p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\"><b><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\">Volume of Productivity</span></b></p><ul><li><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\" style=\"\">Approximately 31.52 thousand metric tons.<br></span></li></ul><p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\"><b><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\"><b><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"\\&quot;MsoNormal\\&quot;\"><br></p>','<ul><li><span lang=\"\\&quot;EN-US\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\" 11.0pt;line-height:106%;mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\"=\"\">The best soil suited to peanut production is well-drained, light colored, loose, friable, sandy 
loam that contains high levels of calcium, a moderate amount of organic matter, and with moderate 
to slightly acidic pH ranging from 5.8 to 6.5.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cucumber&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;don&rsquo;t compete with peanut plants for nutrients. Cucumbers attract bees and ladybugs, which control pests and pollinate crops.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tomato&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;grows tall, providing shade for tomato roots during hot months and fix nitrogen in the soil.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Lettuce&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;is shallow rooted, so it won&rsquo;t compete for nutrients with deeper-rooted plants.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Maize&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;sorghum&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;pearl millet&lt;/b&gt;, and &lt;b&gt;small grain crops&lt;/b&gt;, because they are too tall and can shade the peanut plants, reducing their yield and quality.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Onions&lt;/b&gt; and other members of the&lt;b&gt; Allium family&lt;/b&gt;, because they compete for the same nutrients and water as peanuts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common insect
pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Squirrels&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Whiteflies&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Thrips&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Caterpillars&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Armyworms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;













&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 05:40:19');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (46,28,1,'Onion','<p class=\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in\\\\\\\"><span lang=\\\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\\\">In the
Philippines, onions are commonly known as \\\\\\\"sibuyas.\\\\\\\" This term is
widely used in markets, kitchens, and everyday conversations across the country
when referring to bulbous vegetable.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\">Time of
planting<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><ul><li>Growing between the rainy months of September and December. The best planting season is during October to December, and the harvest season is from January to April.<span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\\\" 11.0pt;line-height:106%;mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p>



</p><p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\">Volume
of Productivity</span></b></p><ul><li>84.90 thousand metric tons<br></li></ul>','<ul><li><span style=\\\"font-family: Tahoma, serif; font-size: 18px;\\\">Sandy loam, and clay loam, as long as there are good drainage facilities and an optimum pH of 6.5  7.5.</span><br></li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Filler Crops&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Onions can significantly benefit your &lt;b&gt;tomato&lt;/b&gt; crops. First, they enhance the fruit&rsquo;s&rsquo; flavor. Second, they confuse pests such as aphids from munching your tomatoes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Peppers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;will reap the same benefits from onion companionship- enhancement of flavor, more-likely seen in hot peppers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Carrots&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;and onions enjoy a symbiotic relationship with each other. Carrots will help protect the onions against onion flies, whereas the onions will mask the carrots from carrot flies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Beans &lt;/b&gt;You shouldn&rsquo;t farm onions or any plant inclusive in the allium family close to any beans type. They are likely to cause stunted growth to the beans.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Peas&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Like beans, peas are legumes. Don&rsquo;t grow onions near any legume plant, including peas.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common insect
pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Thrips&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bulb Mites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leafminers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Purple Blotch&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Pink Roots&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dowy Mildew&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 05:52:52');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (47,28,1,'Garlic','<p class=\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\" style=\\\\\\\"text-indent:.5in\\\\\\\"><span lang=\\\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\\\">In the Philippines, garlic is commonly known
as \\\\\\\"bawang.\\\\\\\" This term is widely used in markets, kitchens, and
everyday conversations across the country when referring to the pungent bulb.
Garlic is a key ingredient in Filipino cuisine, used to add flavor to a variety
of dishes, including sauts, stews, and marinades.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p class=\\\"\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\">Time of
Planting<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><ul><li><span style=\\\"font-family: Tahoma, serif; font-size: 18px;\\\">Dry season, and this typically starts from November until early May.</span><br></li></ul><p>



<b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\\\" line-height:106%;font-family:\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;=\\\"\\\" mso-fareast-font-family:calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:=\\\"\\\" minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\\\"times=\\\"\\\" new=\\\"\\\" roman\\\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;=\\\"\\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:en-us;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\">Volume
of Productivity</span></b></p><ul><li><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\" line-height:106%;font-family:\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;=\\\"\\\" mso-fareast-font-family:calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:=\\\"\\\" minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\\\"times=\\\"\\\" new=\\\"\\\" roman\\\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;=\\\"\\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:en-us;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\">Approximately 5.88 thousand metric tons<br></span></li></ul><p><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\\\" line-height:106%;font-family:\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;=\\\"\\\" mso-fareast-font-family:calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:=\\\"\\\" minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\\\"times=\\\"\\\" new=\\\"\\\" roman\\\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;=\\\"\\\" mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:en-us;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\"><br></span></b><br></p>','<ul><li>Sandy soils with good drainage, a pH 6 to 7, and rich in organic matter (about 5% is ideal).</li></ul><ul><li>Avoid clay, compacted, and reddish soils since they will negatively affect sprouting and bulb formation and may color the skins, reducing the products quality.</li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Fillers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Spinach&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;and garlic make a great pair because they are both cold hardy plants that can share a bed in the spring and fall.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Potato&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;and garlic have been cited to reduce potato blight even more effectively than using fungicides.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Carrots &lt;/b&gt;discourage&amp;nbsp;common garlic pests, and in return garlic keeps away the destructive carrot rust fly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst
Companion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Planting
legumes near garlic can result in an overabundance of nitrogen, which can lead
to poor growth and smaller bulbs.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Like beans, peas are legumes. Don&rsquo;t grow onions near any legume plant, including peas.&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common insect
pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Aphid&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;









&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Scales&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 05:54:58');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (48,28,9,'Chives','<p class=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\"><span lang=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\">In the
Philippines, chives are commonly known as \\\"kuchoay\\\" or \\\"kucai.\\\" These terms are used in markets, kitchens, and everyday
conversations across the country when referring to this herb. Chives, or
kuchoay/kucai, are often used as a flavorful garnish in various Filipino
dishes, providing a mild onion-like taste.<o:p></o:p></span></p>','<p class=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text-align:justify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\">Time of Planting<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><ul><li><span lang=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\" 11.0pt;line-height:106%;mso-ansi-language:en-us\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\">Wet season, and this typically
starts from November until early May.</span></li></ul><p>



</p><p class=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"MsoNormal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\" style=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text-align:justify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"EN-US\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\">Volume of productivity</span></b></p><ul><li>Approximately 33,000 kg/ha.</li></ul>','<ul><li>chives need light, loamy, and sandy soils with good drainage.</li><li>If youre working with soil that has a lot of clay or is very dense, mix in some sand to loosen it up.</li><li>Chives need soil with a pH between 6 and 7.</li><li>Test the soil, and if it is too low, increase the pH by chopping agricultural lime into the soil using a garden trowel or small shovel.</li><li>If it is too high, lower the pH by mixing in a fertilizer with urea phosphate or ammonium nitrate, or by adding compost, manure, or plant litter.</li></ul>','&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Fillers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Cabbage&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;help in preventing the spread of fungal infections throughout the entire plant, which is crucial if you&rsquo;re growing cabbage&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(58, 58, 58); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, BlinkMacSystemFont, &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &amp;quot;Apple Color Emoji&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Emoji&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Segoe UI Symbol&amp;quot;; font-size: 17px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;indoors with lights.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Carrot&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;will provide your chive plant nitrogen, which will promote overall development and increase its resistance to pests like aphids or whiteflies.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tomato&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;reaps the rewards of chive pest management while being protected from aphids, whiteflies, and spider mites.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Worst Companion&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Bulb family similar growth requirements and compete for the same nutrients in the soil.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Planting legumes near chives can result in an overabundance of nitrogen, which can lead to poor growth and smaller bulbs.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Common insect pest&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Aphid&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;Scales&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Whiteflies&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Spider mites&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2023-11-12 05:56:37');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (49,28,9,'Lettuce','<p>Lettuce is commonly known as lechugas which is native to Southern Europe and Western Asia. In the Philippines lettuce is considered as one of the most important salad crops and also used as garnishing for other food preparations.<br></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li>In the Philippines, lettuce can be planted in low elevations during November to December. The quality is best in high elevations (1000 m asl). The growing season for lettuce in the Philippines is from August to January.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><br></p>','<p>Lettuce grows best in soils with a pH of 6 to 6.8 and in a silty clay loam, loam and clay loam soils. Soils with high organic matter are preferred for good water holding capacity.<br></p><p><br></p><p>VOLUME OF PRODUCTIVITY</p><ul><li>5 to 10 tons per hec</li></ul><div><br></div>','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Does well with &lt;b&gt;beet, bush bean, pole bean, cabbage, carrot, cucumber, onion, and radish.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Worst&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Avoid growing lettuce next to &lt;b&gt;broccoli, cabbage, and cauliflower while some varieties of lettuce&lt;/b&gt; may help these cabbage-family crops to grow, these plants have particular root secretions that can prevent lettuce seeds from germinating.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2024-01-10 03:04:29');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (50,29,1,'Taro','<p>Taro is grown as a root crop throughout the humid tropics and is one of the most important food staples in the Pacific. It needs a long, frost-free growing season and plenty of water. Taro is suitable for both wetland and dryland culture. It will grow well in partial shade, making it an excellent understory plant. Flowers are infrequent and it rarely sets seed.<br></p>','<p><b>Time of planting</b></p><ul><li>In places where there is a distinct wet and dry season, planting is done shortly before the start of rainy season.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><br></p><p><b>Volume of productivity</b></p><ul><li><span style=\"white-space: normal;\"><span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>11.7 t/ha</span></li></ul><div><br></div><div><br></div>','<p><b>Soil type and soil pH</b></p><ul><li>Upland taro can be grown on a wide range of soil types, but best results are obtained on deep, well drained, fri able loams with pH 5.56.5. Rocky or stony soils should be avoided to prevent deformed corms and difficult harvesting.</li></ul>','&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler crops&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Plant shade-tolerant vegetables, like &lt;b&gt;ginger, pepper, mustard and sweet potato&lt;/b&gt; underneath tall crops, like &lt;b&gt;cassava, kadios &lt;/b&gt;and vines on trellis, like &lt;b&gt;gourd, squash and winged beans.&lt;/b&gt; This will form a multi-storied plant canopy, which can efficiently use sunshine.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2024-01-11 07:30:27');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (51,28,1,'Snap beans','<p>Snap bean is one of the popular legumes in the Philippines.&nbsp; Snap bean&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">cultivars differ from dry bean cultivars by having&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">thicker walled pods.&nbsp;</span></p><div><br></div>','<p><b>Time of planting</b></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">In places where the climate is cool throughout the year like&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Benguet, snap beans are planted at any time. In other places, they are planted during&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">the cool month usually from November to January. Better yields at low elevation&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">have been obtained with bush and pole type of snap beans from November&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">plantings than from those planted in February.</span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\"><b>Volume of Productivity</b></span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">8-12 tons/hac<br><br></span><br></li></ul>','<p><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\"><b>Soil Type and Soil pH</b></span><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Snap bean thrives best in well-drined, clay loam Soil, rich in organic matter with pH ranging from 5.5 to 7.5.</span><br></li></ul><div><br></div>','&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler companion&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Good company for &lt;b&gt;carrot, celery, corn, eggplant, peas, potato, beets, radish,&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;cucumber.&lt;/b&gt; Beans are great for heavy nitrogen users like corn because beans fix nitrogen from the air into the soil, so the nitrogen used up by the corn are replaced at the end of the season when the bean plants die back.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Worst companion&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Chives, onion and garlic &lt;/b&gt;takes away nitrogen from snap beans.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Insect Pests&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&bull; Cutworm. This insect pest is destructive during the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;seedling stage of beans.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&bull; Leaf miner. This is a serious pest also of garden pea&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;during the dry season. The larvae tunnel into the leaf&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;and eat the chlorophyll leaving only the epidermis.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&bull; Maggots. This is a problem during dry season. The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;young plants wilt as a result of the destruction of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;bark of the stem at the soil line caused by the maggot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;',1,'2024-01-11 07:52:38');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (52,27,9,'Alugbati','<p>Alugbati, is commonly grown for its young shoots which are succulent and can be consumed boiled, fried, or as a green salad. Alugbati, also known as Malabar spinach or Ceylon spinach, is a popular vegetable crop widely cultivated in the Philippines and other tropical regions such as Africa and Souteast Asia.<br></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li>The best time for planting is at the end of the rainy season. Alugbati is propagated through seeds and cutting 20 to 25 cm long. In using cuttings, the leaves are usually removed before planting so as to reduce water loss through transpiration.</li></ul><p><b>Volume of Productivity</b></p><ul><li>50,000 plants/hec</li></ul>','<div><b>Soil type and Soil pH</b></div><div><br></div><ul><li>Alugbati grows well under full sunlight in hot, humid climates and in areas lower than 500 m above sea level. Growth is slow in low temperatures resulting in low yields. Flowering is induced during the short-day months of November to February. Alugbati grows best in sandy loam soils rich in organic matter with pH ranging from 5.5 to 8.0.</li></ul>','&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pest and Disease Management&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Alugbati is generally tolerant to pests and diseases, which makes it easy to grow organically. However, it serves as a host to a number of insect pests such as leafminers and cutworms, which can be managed by regular harvesting. Root-knot nematodes can be minimized by crop rotation with corn and planting of marigold.&amp;nbsp; Alugbati is also tolerant to leaf spot caused by Colletotrichum spp.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;',1,'2024-01-11 08:03:21');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (53,29,1,'Lima Beans','<p>Lima beans are annual plants that belong to the legume family. They have flat, kidney shaped seeds. The plants produce vines that can climb or sprawl, depending on the variety.<br></p>','<p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Time of Planting</span></p><ul><li>Lima beans are warm season crops, so they are typically planted after the last frost in spring when the soil has warmed up.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Volume&nbsp;</span><span style=\"text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">of Productivity</span></span></p><ul><li><span style=\"text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">10,000 to 15,000 tons per hec</span></li></ul>','<div><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Soil type and Soil pH</span></div><div><br></div><ul><li>Lima beans are warm season crops, so they are typically planted after the last frost in spring when the soil has warmed up.&nbsp;</li></ul><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Lima beans prefer well drained, loamy soil with a pH between 6.0 and 7.0.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">They are sensitive to acidic soils, so adding lime may be necessary if the pH is too low.</span></li></ul>','&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Filler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lima beans often do well when planted near crops like&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;corn and potatoes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;These plants provide some shade and support for the lima bean vines.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Worst Companions&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Avoid planting lima beans near onions and garlic, as they may inhibit each other growth.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder; font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Common Insect Pests and Control&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Aphids&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;nsecticidal soap or neem oil can be used to control aphids.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Spider Mites&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;regularly spraying plants with water can help control spider mites.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Cutworms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;collars around the base of young plants can protect them from cutworms.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;',1,'2024-01-11 08:16:38');
INSERT INTO "crops_list" VALUES (54,29,1,'Ginger','<p>Ginger is a tropical flowering plant with green leaves and yellow green flowers. The part of the plant used is the rhizome, an underground stem that is aromatic and spicy.<br></p>','<p><b>Time of Planting</b></p><ul><li>In tropical regions, ginger can be planted throughout the year. In subtropical regions, it is often planted in the spring.<br></li></ul>','<p><b>Soil type and Soil pH</b></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Well drained, loamy soil rich in organic matter is ideal.</span></li></ul><ul><li>Ginger prefers slightly acidic to neutral soil with a pH between 6.0 and 6.5.</li></ul>','&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Filler&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ginger is often grown alongside other companion plants like &lt;b&gt;turmeric and garlic.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Pests&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Aphids, mites, and root knot nematodes can affect ginger.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;',1,'2024-01-11 08:43:03');
